metadata.name: Ambiguous Instances #92
metadata.description:
“Ambiguous Instances” is the sixth collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

Often people use a specific example to argue their point of view. Unfortunately, this means that they can completely make it up or hyperbolise it to benefit their views, which means that it's a completely invalid argument.

Statistics, on the other hand, cannot lie, since they are just pure observations.
That is unless they are completely made up, of course.

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #311
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)

metadata.name: Planetary Orbital #25
metadata.description:
The Planetary Orbital series explores a series of minimalist planets with a planet data printed in the artwork itself. Each planet is given its own name based on hash.
Rotation decided by hash.
Colors generated by hash.
→ Tonal versions have a 50% probability.
→ B/W versions have a 3% probability.
7 different abstractions of planet properties — 5% probability of having all markings present on artwork. 50% probability of having gradient feature.

----------
#planetaryorbital
----------

Original artwork created in p5js. Hope you enjoy your planet.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #929
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: PURZ x CIPOTE - Tunnel Vision #34
metadata.description:
Tunnel Vision by Purz & Cipote

A collaboration between analog and digital sources, using photographs of analog video distortion captured on CRT monitors running through a series of digital generative processing.

Variations include:

- Source Textures
- Grids
- Grid Size
- Grid Complexity
- Mirror
- Flipping
- Texture Location
- Texture Mirroring

Special Editions:

- Gameboy
- CRT (PS1)
- CRT (PS2)
- Lens Flare Explosion
- Dithered Pixelation
- Pixelated Dream

metadata.name: Tesseract #25
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.
